x4freetext: WNR at LAMPF
Thin cobalt target (3.79mg/cm2)
Incident energy determined by time-of-flight,
9.123-m flight path.
Energy calibrated using 228,229Th alpha-particle
source.
dE detector was thin window low
pressure proportional counter, E detectors were surface
barrier Si detectors. Four telescopes were placed
at angles of 30, 60, 90 and 135 deg.
Neutron flux was measured with a fission
chamber containing both 235U and 238U, places at
10.1 m from neutron source
monitoring via FF - for U-238 monitor
Corrected for energy loss in target, and in windows and
gas of delta E counter.
Statistical uncertainties.
Overall normalization uncertainty estimated to be 8%
due to geometry and possible non-uniformity of the
235U fission deposit used for flux normalization.
The resolution of the gas counters was not sufficient
to separate isotopes of hydrogen ions or to separate
3He from alpha particles. (R.C.Haight, 2012-05-30)
